Class DiceRolls

  • java.lang.Object
    • MiniGame
      • DiceRolls

  • public class DiceRolls
extends MiniGame
    Instances of DiceRolls represent a type of minigame the player could play to battle villains. Instances are created when a villain choses to play Dice Rolls.

    • Method Detail

      • roll

        public void roll()
        Carries out one round of a dice rolls game. Sets heroRoll and villainRoll to new randomised numbers, determines the result and whether or not a Tiebreaker was used. Removes a Tiebreaker from the hero if it is used, and removes all Sets hasWon to true if the hero wins the game.

      • determineResult

        private void determineResult()
        Takes the hero's roll and the villian's roll, and determines the result of the game. If the game is a tie, checks for TieBreaker power-ups. If the hero has won, sets hasWon to true, otherwise it remains false. If the game is finished (either hero or villain has won), sets gameFinished to true, otherwise it remains false.

      • generateRoll

        private int generateRoll()
        Generates a random die roll between 1 and NUM_DICE_SIDES inclusive.
        Returns:
        The random die roll.
